_rawBody:
Nora makes a birthday cake.

\begin{parts}
    \item Nora has a packet containing $250\,\text{g}$ of cherries.

    She uses $\dfrac{7}{10}$ of the cherries in the cake.

    Find the mass of cherries she has left.
    \AnswerLine[][g]
    \Marks{2}

    \item The cake is made by putting a small cylinder of cake on top of a large cylinder of cake.

    The radius of the large cylinder is $15\,\text{cm}$.

    The radius of the small cylinder is $8\,\text{cm}$.

    The height of each cylinder is $10\,\text{cm}$.

    \begin{center}
    \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=0.3]
        % Large cylinder
        \draw (0,0) ellipse (3 and 0.6);
        \draw (-3,0) -- (-3,2);
        \draw (3,0) -- (3,2);
        \draw (0,2) ellipse (3 and 0.6);

        % Small cylinder on top
        \draw (0,2) ellipse (1.6 and 0.32);
        \draw (-1.6,2) -- (-1.6,4);
        \draw (1.6,2) -- (1.6,4);
        \draw (0,4) ellipse (1.6 and 0.32);

        % Dimensions
        \draw[<->] (4,0) -- (4,2) node[midway, right] {$10\,\text{cm}$};
        \draw[<->] (2.5,2) -- (2.5,4) node[midway, right] {$10\,\text{cm}$};
        \draw[<->] (-3,-1) -- (3,-1) node[midway, below] {$15\,\text{cm}$};
        \draw[<->] (-1.6,4.8) -- (1.6,4.8) node[midway, above] {$8\,\text{cm}$};

        \node at (7,2) {\footnotesize NOT TO};
        \node at (7,1.3) {\footnotesize SCALE};
    \end{tikzpicture}
    \end{center}

    \begin{subparts}
        \subpart Calculate the total volume of the cake.
        \AnswerLine[][cm$^3$]
        \Marks{3}

        \subpart Nora wraps a ribbon around the large cylinder.

        The ribbon is $4\,\text{cm}$ longer than needed to go all the way around this cylinder.

        Calculate the length of this ribbon.
        \AnswerLine[][cm]
        \Marks{3}
    \end{subparts}

    \item The mass, $m$ grams, of the cake is $1250\,\text{g}$, correct to the nearest $10\,\text{g}$.

    Complete this statement about the value of $m$.
    \AnswerLine[][$\leqslant m <$]
    \Marks{2}
\end{parts}

